info.title: r/SpaceX
info.description: r/SpaceX is an open Source REST API for SpaceX launch, rocket, core, capsule, Starlink, launchpad, and landing pad data. r/SpaceX is not affiliated, associated, authorized, endorsed by, or in any way officially connected with Space Exploration Technologies Corp (SpaceX), or any of its subsidiaries or its affiliates. The names SpaceX as well as related names, marks, emblems and images are registered trademarks of their respective owners.

get.description: Detailed info for all serialized Dragon capsules.
Detailed info for a serialized Dragon capsule.

query.description: Accepts any valid MongoDB find() query.
query.title: Query

select.description: Fields to return (by default returns all fields).
select.title: Select

populate.description: Paths which should be populated with other documents.
populate.title: Populate

lean.description: Should return plain javascript objects instead of Mongoose documents.
lean.title: Lean

leanWithId.description: If lean and leanWithId are true adds id field with string representation of _id to every document.
leanWithId.title: Lean With Id

offset.description: Use offset or page to set skip position.
offset.title: Offset

customLabels.description: Developers can provide custom labels for manipulating the response data.
customLabels.title: Custom Labels

pagination.description: If pagination is set to false it will return all docs without adding limit condition.
pagination.title: Pagination

useEstimatedCount.description: Enable estimatedDocumentCount for larger datasets. Does not count based on given query so the count will match entire collection size.
useEstimatedCount.title: Use Estimated Count

useCustomCountFn.description: Enable custom function for count datasets.

forceCountFn.description: Set this to true if you need to support $geo queries.

allowDiskUse.description: Set this to true which allows the MongoDB server to use more than 100 MB for query. This option can let you work around QueryExceededMemoryLimitNoDiskUseAllowed errors from the MongoDB server.
